A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Law Enforcement Officers – Body–Worn Cameras – Requirements
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing a recording of a body–worn camera worn by a law
4 enforcement officer to be used as evidence in any administrative, judicial, legislative,
5 or disciplinary proceeding; requiring a custodian to deny inspection of a recording
6 made with the use of a body–worn camera of a law enforcement officer, subject to
7 certain exceptions; establishing minimum requirements for a body–worn camera
8 policy for a law enforcement agency and the model policy created by the Maryland
9 Police Training and Standards Commission; requiring certain law enforcement
10 agencies to require the use of body–worn cameras by certain law enforcement officers
11 on or before a certain date; requiring each law enforcement agency to submit certain
12 information to the Commission each year; requiring the Commission to submit a
13 certain report each year; and generally relating to the use of body–worn cameras by
14 law enforcement officers.
